ENTRY            F0691   20251223   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0691001   20251223   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 12         37
TITLE      New measurement and analysis of the 7Be(p,gamma)8B
           cross section
AUTHOR     (F.Hammache,G.Bogaert,P.Aguer,C.Angulo,S.Barhoumi,
           L.Brillard,J.F.Chemin,G.Claverie,A.Coc,M.Hussonnois,
           M.Jacotin,J.Kiener,A.Lefebvre,J.N.Scheurer,J.P.Thibaud,
           E.Virassamynaiken)
INSTITUTE  (2FR CSN,2FR GRA,2FR PAR,3ALGUHB)
REFERENCE  (J,PRL,80,928,1998)
FACILITY   (VDG,2FR GRA)
DETECTOR   (HPGE)
METHOD     (GSPEC,BCINT)
            The 7Be(p,gamma)8B cross section was measured by
           detecting the delayed alpha particles following the
           beta+ decay of 8B.
MONITOR    ((MONIT)3-LI-7(D,P)3-LI-8,,SIG) The beam energy was
           calibrated to +-0.1% from thick target yield curves
           at resonances in the 19F(p,alpha gammma)16O
            [27Al(p,gamma)28Si] reaction at proton energies of
           340.46 keV and 871.11 keV (632.6 keV, 991.8 keV].
           Effective reaction energies were determined from
           measurements of the target thickness and of the
           carbon buildup by consistent Rutherford
           backscattering measurements and (d,p) reaction
           analysis of 12C,16O performed many times during the
           course of the experiment.
MONIT-REF  ((MONIT)A0640001,F.Strieder+,J,ZP/A,355,209,1996)
           In the present work, authors adopt the
           value 147 +- 11 mb recommended by Adelberger et al.
           This value is very close to that given by
           Strieder et al., 146 +- 5 mb, except for the error bar.
SAMPLE     The targets consist of 7Be oxide deposited on Pt disk.
           Target thickness is 4.0+-0.4 keV at a proton energy
           of 441 keV.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Relative error
HISTORY    (20040517C)
           (20251223A) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           DATA-ERR -> ERR-1.
ENDBIB              37
COMMON               5          3
EN-ERR     MONIT      MONIT-ERR  EN-ERR-DIG ERR-DIG
PER-CENT   MB         MB         MEV        B*EV
        0.1      147.0       11.0      0.001       0.02
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           44
SUBENT        F0691002   20251223   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  5          7
REACTION   (4-BE-7(P,G)5-B-8,,SIG,,SFC)
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Four surface barrier detectors 30 um thick
           were used.
SAMPLE     Target activity was increased to 26.9+-0.5 mCi.
STATUS     (CURVE,,F.Hammache+,J,PRL,80,928,1998) Fig. 3
           (COREL,F0691003) Data measured with 10.4 mCi sample
HISTORY    (20251223U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB               7
